div.div: Goukon ni Ittara Onna ga Inakatta Hanashi

College student Tokiwa gets invited to a mixer by his female classmate Suo. But when he arrives with his friends, they're greeted by three dazzlingly handsome men?! But as the two groups get to know each other, they find themselves getting closer in unexpected ways. (Source: MANGA UP!) Note: Each episode streamed 1 week early on ABEMA. The original TV broadcast started on October 4th 2024.
MASHLE: Kami Shinkakusha Kouho Senbatsu Shiken-hen

The second season of MASHLE, adapting the Divine Visionary Candidate Exam Arc. After Mash Burnedead's clash with Magia Lupus, the secret about his powers is now out in the open. The short-lived celebration ends when the Bureau of Magic summons Mash before an audience of Divine Visionaries, who collectively decree Mash should reap the consequences and die. However, an evil shadow organization called Innocent Zero hijacks the inquiry to demand that Mash be kept alive. Mash proves that he is capable of dealing with Innocent Zero, but the Divine Visionaries' verdict remains unchanged. Luckily, Mash finds unexpected allies in Divine Visionary Rayne Ames and Headmaster Wahlberg Baigan, and they successfully defer his execution until Innocent Zero is defeated. Mash is now allowed to live under one condition: he must be selected as the Divine Visionary candidate by the year's end. (Source: MAL Rewrite)
Kaiko sareta Ankoku Heishi (30-dai) no Slow na Second Life
Comedy, Ecchi, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

Dariel is a dark soldier in the Demon Kings army in his 30s and unable to use magic who was suddenly dismissed! Kicked out of his hometown, Dariel drifted into a human village where adventurer skills that arent bestowed onto demons bursted into bloom! Imhuman? Then, a village girl launches a fierce attack to get her hands on and subdue him, a novice adventurer, who fell into her lap?! His second chance at life and he still cant relax has just begun!
(Source: K Manga)

Guyangcheon betrayed the sect and became a demon under Cheonma. Living as a demon, he committed numerous evil deeds against his will under Cheonma's orders and ended up living a life filled with regret.
The Great Battle of Jeongma started by Cheonma. The long and hellish Great Battle of Jeongma came to an end due to Wisul-ah, who cut down Cheonma, who had even made the three great beings of Jeongpa kneel. Guyangcheon, who had been committing evil deeds as a demon, was captured by Jeongpa and tortured. While passing on information about the Demonic Cult to Wisul-ah with his last remaining conscience, he ended up dying due to Cheonma's prohibition.
However, for some reason, Guyangcheon regresses to the point where he first met Wisul-ah in the past. Realizing that the return was not a dream, Guyangcheon decides to live quietly so as not to do anything he would regret, but for some reason, the people he had bad ties with in his past life start to get entangled one by one, contrary to his intentions.
(Source: KakaoPage, translated)
